            <title><![CDATA[Exchange of missile strikes between Israel and Iran threatens fragile ceasefire]]></title>
            <link>https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/exchange-of-missile-strikes-between-israel-and-iran-threatens-fragile-ceasefire</link>
            <description><![CDATA[Israel and Iran traded long-range missile strikes for the first time since the ceasefire went into effect two months ago. Both countries appear to have agreed to stop their attacks, but not before sparking fears of a return to full combat in the region. Now, Trump and regional mediators are scrambling to salvage a deal to end the war with Iran. Ali Rogin reports.]]></description>
